<isis lang="en">

    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Hood Seal</title>
        <para>Release the hood latches on each side and raise the hood to the full tilt position. Locate the hood seal
            on the forward edge of the cowl (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006144">Figure 144, Item 1</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Beginning on the driver side of the cowl, locate the christmas tree type mounting clip (
                <hotlnk document="s47006_71.xml" xrefid="f47006114">Figure 114, Item 2</hotlnk>) and pull the seal
                upward to release the clip.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grip the hood seal and lift in upward direction away from the cowl surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull upward to remove the seal from the entire lip of the cowl.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006144" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006144.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 144. Hood Seal Removal - Driver Side Shown</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HOOD SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CHRISTMAS TREE FASTENER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. COWL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. CHRISTMAS TREE MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
